        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 4:15PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 414 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Stonewall, or 26 miles west of Trinidad. This thunderstorm was nearly
stationary. This storm is producing localized heavy rain.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stonewall.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
